Garden Centre Asks to Extend Debt Maturity, Telegraph Says

-- B y   J a s o n   W e b b
-- 
2011-04-30T13:52:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/garden-centre-group-asks-to-extend-debt-maturity-telegraph-says.html
Garden Centre Group, owner of
Wyevale Garden Centres Plc, the U.K.’s biggest plant seller, is
in talks with Lloyds Banking Group Plc to extend the maturity of
its debts, newspaper The Daily Telegraph reported today.  Wyevale now has 116 centers, according to a Regulatory News
Service statement on Dec. 16 from Hereford, England-based
Wyevale.  “The bank is in positive discussions to extend the terms
of the debt for the Garden Centre,” a Lloyds spokesperson, who
declined to be named in accordance with company policy, said in
a phone interview, “The Garden Centre Group continues to trade
well and has the bank’s support.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Webb in  London  at 
